1
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:15,515
Natsumi!

2
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,393
Natsumi!

3
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:21,020
Sorry!

4
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:24,482
Natsumi!

5
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:25,442
Hey!

6
00:00:25,525 --> 00:00:28,028
-What are you doing? It's too dangerous!
-My daughter…

7
00:00:28,111 --> 00:00:30,488
-My daughter is inside!
-What?

8
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:32,407
Natsumi!

9
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,185
LOVE-CHAN COOKIE

10
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:05,315
All right.

11
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:06,900
See you all later.

12
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:08,401
-See you.
-Good night.

13
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:09,444
What?

14
00:01:09,527 --> 00:01:10,612
What's the rush?

15
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:12,572
I just have a feeling.

16
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:13,615
A feeling?

17
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:17,368
A feeling that if I stay,
I'll get caught up in work.

18
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:19,496
Don't jinx it at this hour.

19
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:21,790
It was peaceful today, wasn't it?

20
00:01:21,873 --> 00:01:25,293
This is exactly when
sudden requests come in, right?

21
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:27,462
That's what you call a sixth sense.

22
00:01:28,046 --> 00:01:31,382
It's said that the insular cortex
in the brain is involved in that.

23
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:32,383
The insular cortex?

24
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:36,012
It is a region involved in various
internal sensations of the body.

25
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:38,139
What seems like a hunch

26
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:42,644
is actually detecting and anticipating
a change, based on past experiences.

27
00:01:42,727 --> 00:01:44,687
So there is a proper basis for it.

28
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:46,356
I'm done too.

29
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,273
Hey, wait!

30
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:48,399
See you.

31
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:57,534
Oh, good evening.

32
00:01:57,617 --> 00:01:58,576
Hey.

33
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,787
Kerosene has been detected.

34
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:02,455
It has to be arson.

35
00:02:02,539 --> 00:02:05,125
-Is this the body?
-Yes.

36
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:07,210
It carbonized due to high temperatures,

37
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:10,213
and then the house collapsed,
crushing the remains.

38
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:15,385
The skeletal structure
hasn't retained its original form either.

39
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:17,137
According to eyewitnesses,

40
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:20,223
five-year-old Natsumi Sata
wasn't able to escape the house,

41
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,142
and her mother, Haruka Sata,

42
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:24,561
reportedly went into the fire
to try and save her.

43
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:28,314
-Wait! Just wait!
-Let me through!

44
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:36,030
That is Haruka's husband, Yasuyuki Sata.

45
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:38,491
Excuse us.

46
00:02:39,075 --> 00:02:40,368
We're the police.

47
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:43,580
Could we ask you a few questions?

48
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,665
What on earth happened?

49
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:48,042
Haruka and Natsumi are okay, right?

50
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:50,211
Where are they?

51
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:52,589
We're still investigating the details.

52
00:02:53,089 --> 00:02:53,923
But we've found

53
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:56,384
burned skeletal parts.

54
00:02:56,968 --> 00:03:01,014
Eyewitnesses report seeing
Haruka and Natsumi taken by the fire.

55
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,645
That's not true.

56
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:11,399
It can't be true.

57
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:15,737
Natsumi! Haruka!

58
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,864
Please calm down.

59
00:03:22,118 --> 00:03:23,453
There's no way…

60
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:26,623
It's not true.

61
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,752
Sir.

62
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:35,048
I'm sorry for asking this
at such a difficult time.

63
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:39,260
Do you recognize this?

64
00:03:40,428 --> 00:03:42,096
It's a wedding ring, isn't it?

65
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:49,520
This belongs to Haruka, correct?

66
00:03:54,692 --> 00:03:56,236
I promise you.

67
00:03:57,612 --> 00:04:01,157
The police will get to the bottom of this.

68
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:18,716
All the soft tissue was burnt away.

69
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,052
We have to handle this quite carefully.

70
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:23,805
I wonder if any teeth marks are left.

71
00:04:23,888 --> 00:04:26,307
Can an accurate identification
really be made?

72
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:31,354
Regardless of the body's condition,
a piece of the truth is always there.

73
00:04:40,571 --> 00:04:41,864
Let's begin.

74
00:04:49,163 --> 00:04:52,542
Personal identification
proved to be extremely difficult.

75
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,085
However, this part,

76
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:56,587
although severely damaged,

77
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,965
appears to be the lower first molar.

78
00:04:59,048 --> 00:05:01,843
This is likely
a metallic inlay restoration.

79
00:05:01,926 --> 00:05:05,471
With this, we managed to match
the teeth marks with the dental charts,

80
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:08,975
confirming that the body
belongs to Haruka Sata.

81
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:10,852
You did a great job identifying it.

82
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:14,397
Even looking at the femur,
which withstood the most,

83
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,399
there is no mistake
that it's a female in her thirties.

84
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:18,443
So, what about the child?

85
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,362
About that…

86
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,658
We couldn't find her.

87
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:26,784
What?

88
00:05:28,286 --> 00:05:34,125
Currently, the gathered remains
are for only one person, Haruka.

89
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,918
No way.

90
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:40,757
But Haruka went into the fire
to save Natsumi, didn't she?

91
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:44,052
A child calling for help inside the flames
was also witnessed.

92
00:05:44,135 --> 00:05:45,595
However,

93
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:48,264
from those remains…

94
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:55,104
Since she was still a small child,

95
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:58,107
could it be that the bones
were completely destroyed?

96
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:03,196
Even at the maximum temperature of
a crematorium, fragments of bone remain.

97
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:07,450
It is impossible for absolutely
no trace to be left behind.

98
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:09,410
Did she completely turn to ash?

99
00:06:09,494 --> 00:06:10,828
Even if reduced to ash,

100
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:13,206
inorganic matter
derived from bone remains.

101
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:16,501
It becomes a powder,
but some trace should still be left.

102
00:06:16,584 --> 00:06:18,044
It doesn't add up.

103
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:20,379
Of course, I suppose
there is a possibility

104
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:25,468
that she escaped the flames on her own
and is alive somewhere.

105
00:06:25,551 --> 00:06:27,678
There were many onlookers
around the scene,

106
00:06:27,762 --> 00:06:29,806
and a fire truck arrived
on the back street.

107
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:32,183
Nobody witnessed a child escaping.

108
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:35,478
Then, where is Natsumi?

109
00:06:37,939 --> 00:06:40,149
She vanished into the fire.

110
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:42,235
Is that it?

111
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:45,488
For now,

112
00:06:46,864 --> 00:06:48,199
it's a mystery.

113
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:51,244
Kozue Tanahara.

114
00:06:51,327 --> 00:06:55,748
You were the first caller
for yesterday's fire, correct?

115
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:56,833
Yes.

116
00:06:56,916 --> 00:07:01,170
It seems you reported
that your friend jumped into the flames.

117
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:02,880
A friend?

118
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:03,881
Right.

119
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:08,427
Haruka and I have been partners
in badminton since we were young.

120
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,888
We were always together.

121
00:07:11,472 --> 00:07:13,850
It seems like you did rather well.

122
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:16,853
What's this photo?

123
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:20,231
That was when we went
to a hot spring last year.

124
00:07:22,692 --> 00:07:25,278
You were with Haruka
yesterday as well, correct?

125
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:31,075
Please tell us what happened.

126
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:36,747
<i>Yesterday,</i>

127
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:41,752
<i>we were driving in my car</i>
<i>just to get a change of pace.</i>

128
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:43,296
<i>And then,</i>

129
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:45,590
<i>when I dropped her off at her house…</i>

130
00:07:46,757 --> 00:07:47,884
Help!

131
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:49,802
It's hot!

132
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:54,474
Mom!

133
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:55,475
Haruka?

134
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:56,851
Help me!

135
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:58,561
Natsumi!

136
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,149
Natsumi!

137
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:05,693
-Hey! What are you doing?
-My daughter…

138
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:07,069
It's hot!

139
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:08,905
My daughter is inside!

140
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:10,072
It's too dangerous!

141
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:11,240
Natsumi!

142
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:21,542
I can't believe it.

143
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:24,545
You didn't find Natsumi?

144
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:31,219
Just to confirm,

145
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:35,181
Natsumi was left home alone?

146
00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:37,016
Yes.

147
00:08:39,393 --> 00:08:41,395
Where did you go?

148
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:45,149
We didn't really have any destination.

149
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:46,359
We just wanted to talk.

150
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:48,069
Just talk?

151
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,948
Like about what happened at kindergarten.

152
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:53,950
And about Yasuyuki.

153
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,993
Who is Yasuyuki?

154
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:57,787
<i>Haruka's husband.</i>

155
00:08:58,287 --> 00:09:01,165
Yasuyuki and I
were originally high school classmates,

156
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:02,917
and I introduced him to Haruka.

157
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:07,129
So you were the one
who brought them together.

158
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:18,558
Are we about done now?

159
00:09:19,183 --> 00:09:21,018
I have an appointment coming up.

160
00:09:21,102 --> 00:09:23,479
You're not taking time off from work, huh?

161
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:24,981
What?

162
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:27,024
Your close friend passed away.

163
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:29,443
You must be shaken up.

164
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:35,283
Well, I'm busy.

165
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:40,246
More importantly, have Natsumi's remains
still not been found?

166
00:09:40,329 --> 00:09:41,831
Please find them quickly.

167
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:44,792
Of course.

168
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,335
I'm counting on you.

169
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:48,796
Of course.

170
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:50,590
We will do our best.

171
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:58,723
<i>Natsumi was only five.</i>

172
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:02,018
Leaving such a young child alone
just for a casual drive is strange.

173
00:10:02,101 --> 00:10:05,104
-They could've taken her along.
-Well, that's true.

174
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:06,022
That's true.

175
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:09,442
And her friend died,
yet she didn't ask a single question.

176
00:10:09,525 --> 00:10:12,028
"Why did she die?" "Who did it?"
People ask that.

177
00:10:12,653 --> 00:10:14,030
Are you saying

178
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,407
you suspect Kozue is the arsonist?

179
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:24,081
Investigate Kozue Tanahara thoroughly.

180
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:24,999
Yes, ma'am.

181
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:38,054
The next batch has arrived.

182
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:39,096
All right.

183
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:41,349
What?

184
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:44,644
Are we checking all of this to see
if we find Natsumi's remains?

185
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:48,105
They said they had everything
that looked strange transported here.

186
00:10:48,189 --> 00:10:50,650
This is definitely not bone.

187
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:52,443
Right this way.

188
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:56,030
These are Haruka's parents.

189
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:06,624
Is this

190
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,668
our daughter?

191
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:11,962
Most likely.

192
00:11:13,672 --> 00:11:15,049
What about Nat-chan?

193
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,677
She hasn't been found yet.

194
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:59,009
Haruka would always send us photos.

195
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:03,013
Most of them were of Nat-chan.

196
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,268
She's so cute.

197
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:10,646
She took everything,

198
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:13,315
anything that could be a memento.

199
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:18,737
She often complained
that she had too many things at home.

200
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,030
Just the other day,

201
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:23,325
she brought a memento box to our house.

202
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:24,952
A memento box?

203
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:31,500
If it's all right, could we borrow that?

204
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:32,918
What?

205
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:37,381
It seems Natsumi's remains
still haven't been found.

206
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:40,801
Is it even possible not to find them
after searching this much?

207
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:42,219
I wonder.

208
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:46,223
Could a kidnapper
have taken advantage of the fire?

209
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:49,018
It's not impossible. But…

210
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:53,522
something feels off.

211
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:56,984
I forgot to mention.

212
00:12:57,485 --> 00:13:00,362
I was staking out
Kozue Tanahara's apartment.

213
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:04,450
I know, about you and Haruka.

214
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:05,993
And you?

215
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:08,954
You're relieved, aren't you?

216
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:11,207
What?

217
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:14,502
You wanted to break up with her, right?

218
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:18,255
With this, the obstacle is finally gone.

219
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:21,509
You…

220
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:22,968
Aren't you glad?

221
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:27,723
<i>It seems the two of them</i>
<i>were having an affair.</i>

222
00:13:27,806 --> 00:13:30,267
A witness report came
from Yasuyuki's colleague

223
00:13:30,351 --> 00:13:34,772
that he brought a woman along
to his business trip destination.

224
00:13:35,856 --> 00:13:39,235
Out of growing love and hatred
for her best friend's husband,

225
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:42,821
Kozue Tanahara killed Natsumi,
who became an obstacle, by arson.

226
00:13:42,905 --> 00:13:46,283
Furthermore, she enticed Haruka
to save Natsumi,

227
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:48,410
causing her death.

228
00:13:51,372 --> 00:13:53,916
So, what do you think?

229
00:14:02,716 --> 00:14:03,551
Hey.

230
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:06,470
Couldn't this potentially be
a child's temporal bone?

231
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,433
It looks like an adult's cheekbone to me.

232
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:15,521
No, but, Haruka fractured a bone
last month from falling down the stairs.

233
00:14:15,604 --> 00:14:18,649
If it's her cheekbone,
shouldn't there be a surgical plate?

234
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:23,904
Is it this one?

235
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:25,322
Hey.

236
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:28,200
It's this one.

237
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:29,451
MEDICAL RECORD

238
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:31,120
FIXED CHEEK WITH SURGICAL PLATE

239
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:32,454
FELL DOWN STAIRS AT HER HOME

240
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:33,789
FELL DOWN STAIRS

241
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:36,750
In any case, it's not a child's bone.

242
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:37,710
It's not, right?

243
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:39,420
-It's not.
-It's impossible!

244
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:43,173
Dr. Masumi.

245
00:14:43,757 --> 00:14:47,636
It seems Natsumi's remains
really can't be found after all.

246
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,431
Is that so?

247
00:14:51,181 --> 00:14:53,017
Huh? What's this?

248
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:56,186
Oh, it's Natsumi's memento box.

249
00:14:58,439 --> 00:15:00,065
-So cute.
-Wow.

250
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:01,984
Oh, that's right.

251
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:03,152
Look.

252
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:05,571
What is that?

253
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:07,656
It's an umbilical cord.

254
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:09,742
Oh, from when Natsumi was born?

255
00:15:09,825 --> 00:15:10,659
Yes.

256
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:12,453
I figured she would have kept it.

257
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:14,538
This will be useful too.

258
00:15:15,122 --> 00:15:16,457
Useful?

259
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:19,543
To match Natsumi's DNA.

260
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:22,046
Please test if a sample can be collected.

261
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:23,213
Okay.

262
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:27,384
Ms. Kiryu.

263
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:30,804
Please go to the police station
and get the list of missing persons.

264
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:33,891
A similar case
might provide some sort of hint.

265
00:15:33,974 --> 00:15:35,893
Right, I'm on it.

266
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:40,397
MISSING PERSON REPORT

267
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:43,233
I haven't been able to contact my daughter
for three days.

268
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:45,819
Her workplace says
they can't reach her either.

269
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:47,446
That is worrying.

270
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:50,741
Do you remember what
she might have been wearing?

271
00:15:50,824 --> 00:15:52,326
Supervisor!

272
00:15:55,704 --> 00:15:58,707
I'd have it sent to you
if you'd asked me about it.

273
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:00,584
I'm sorry.

274
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:05,673
So, how is the case going?

275
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:08,592
Any clues?

276
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:21,397
Where could Natsumi have disappeared to?

277
00:16:28,195 --> 00:16:29,363
Ms. Dojima?

278
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:34,451
It's just…

279
00:16:37,579 --> 00:16:38,872
The police

280
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:43,377
exist to protect people's loved ones.

281
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:48,924
People's loved ones…

282
00:16:54,513 --> 00:16:56,015
Hurry up.

283
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:58,142
Yes, ma'am.

284
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:02,855
Here is the list of missing persons.

285
00:17:02,938 --> 00:17:03,939
Thank you very much.

286
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:06,358
Well, I'm heading out for the day.

287
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:08,068
Oh? It's still early.

288
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,699
I'm going to meet a man.

289
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:16,035
What? A man?

290
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:20,039
Oh, wow.

291
00:17:21,623 --> 00:17:23,751
Ms. Dojima met someone nice, huh?

292
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:26,295
Well…

293
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:28,255
That's not what she meant.

294
00:17:29,256 --> 00:17:30,090
What?

295
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:32,217
He's a senior detective.

296
00:17:33,093 --> 00:17:35,554
She says he always looked after her.

297
00:17:35,637 --> 00:17:39,141
What she just said was also a teaching
from that senior officer.

298
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:43,020
Despite how she may seem,
when she was young,

299
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:46,774
she didn't do well in the male-dominated
police force, and it troubled her.

300
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:48,984
<i>At that time,</i>

301
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:51,820
<i>she had failed to apprehend a suspect.</i>

302
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:01,413
I heard you let the suspect get away.

303
00:18:03,707 --> 00:18:05,250
I am very sorry.

304
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,462
What's wrong with that?

305
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,089
What?

306
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,803
You were protecting the family
present at the scene

307
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:17,096
and let him go, right?

308
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,101
That's fine.

309
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:27,106
We are here to protect
people's loved ones.

310
00:18:29,149 --> 00:18:30,734
You're suited to be a detective.

311
00:18:32,402 --> 00:18:35,572
You probably won't get promoted, though.

312
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:37,324
Just like me.

313
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:06,937
<i>But that senior officer,</i>

314
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:11,316
<i>while trying to protect a child</i>
<i>from a random attacker…</i>

315
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:18,031
<i>was killed in the line of duty.</i>

316
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:24,830
<i>Since then, whenever something happens,</i>
<i>she goes to his grave.</i>

317
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:30,335
I think he's the only person
Ms. Dojima can ask for advice from.

318
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:10,125
MAHO KIRYU

319
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:24,097
Dr. Masumi!

320
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:27,935
Look at this.

321
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:29,645
-Ms. Dojima!
-What?

322
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:33,106
Regarding Kozue Tanahara,
she's taking paid leave starting tomorrow.

323
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:35,067
Oh, really?

324
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:36,944
Do you think she intends to flee?

325
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:38,570
Seems suspicious, right?

326
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:39,905
-That's true.
-Also--

327
00:20:39,988 --> 00:20:42,157
Tell me once you've found any evidence.

328
00:20:43,158 --> 00:20:44,201
I have.

329
00:20:45,327 --> 00:20:49,498
One hour before the arson occurred,
Kozue Tanahara purchased kerosene.

330
00:20:51,875 --> 00:20:54,461
Why don't you bring that up first?!

331
00:20:54,544 --> 00:20:55,420
Sorry!

332
00:20:57,130 --> 00:21:00,133
We extracted DNA from both
the umbilical cord and the remains

333
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:04,012
to perform an STR analysis,
and there were ten mismatches.

334
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:05,889
Excuse me?

335
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:09,893
In other words, biologically,
there is no parent-child relationship.

336
00:21:09,977 --> 00:21:11,103
What?

337
00:21:11,687 --> 00:21:13,981
Dr. Masumi, what does this mean?

338
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:24,533
DENTAL RECORDS

339
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:48,890
<i>Her mother, Haruka Sata,</i>
<i>reportedly went into the fire.</i>

340
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:51,560
<i>The gathered remains</i>
<i>are for only one person.</i>

341
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:53,103
<i>I have an appointment coming up.</i>

342
00:21:53,186 --> 00:21:55,981
<i>We managed to match the teeth marks</i>
<i>with the dental charts.</i>

343
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:10,329
Please examine the remains once more.

344
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:14,583
Could it be…

345
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:17,127
The pieces

346
00:22:18,253 --> 00:22:20,047
might be coming together.

347
00:22:39,024 --> 00:22:40,275
Hello.

348
00:22:40,358 --> 00:22:41,943
Do you have a moment?

349
00:23:00,754 --> 00:23:02,089
Sorry to keep you waiting.

350
00:23:02,672 --> 00:23:04,883
Sorry, I know you were about to go out.

351
00:23:06,218 --> 00:23:08,178
Where were you planning to go?

352
00:23:09,971 --> 00:23:11,473
Nowhere in particular.

353
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:14,976
A lot has happened,
just wanted to refresh myself.

354
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,728
Either way, what is this about?

355
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:20,107
We have found out

356
00:23:20,607 --> 00:23:23,860
that the deceased body was not Haruka.

357
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,160
The victim's identity

358
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:34,329
is Miwa Tateno.

359
00:23:35,789 --> 00:23:39,918
She is a high school classmate
of yours and Yasuyuki's.

360
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:46,049
Miwa's whereabouts had been unknown
since the day of that fire.

361
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:49,094
I haven't been able to contact my daughter
for three days.

362
00:23:49,177 --> 00:23:50,095
MIWA TATENO

363
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:51,763
That is only natural.

364
00:23:52,556 --> 00:23:53,723
Because

365
00:23:54,724 --> 00:23:59,646
the body found at the scene of the fire
was not Haruka's,

366
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:03,358
but Miwa's.

367
00:24:08,155 --> 00:24:09,322
<i>As you are friends,</i>

368
00:24:09,406 --> 00:24:13,743
<i>both of them were visiting</i>
<i>the dental clinic you manage.</i>

369
00:24:14,744 --> 00:24:17,289
<i>Using your position,</i>

370
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:19,541
<i>you swapped the dental charts</i>

371
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,960
<i>and disguised Miwa's body</i>

372
00:24:22,043 --> 00:24:24,796
<i>as Haruka's body.</i>

373
00:24:27,382 --> 00:24:28,884
I don't know anything about that.

374
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:30,343
That's nonsense.

375
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:35,182
The first thing I found strange
was the photo from the hot spring trip.

376
00:24:35,932 --> 00:24:39,394
<i>In that photo,</i>
<i>Haruka was not wearing a wedding ring.</i>

377
00:24:39,477 --> 00:24:42,898
<i>It seems she hadn't worn a ring</i>
<i>for several years.</i>

378
00:24:43,481 --> 00:24:48,653
Then why was she wearing it
at the time of the fire?

379
00:24:52,115 --> 00:24:53,700
That's what made me think.

380
00:24:54,201 --> 00:24:58,663
Did someone perhaps
deliberately put the ring on Miwa

381
00:24:58,747 --> 00:25:00,624
to disguise her?

382
00:25:04,586 --> 00:25:08,006
There is only one person
who could make such a disguise

383
00:25:08,089 --> 00:25:11,843
using a wedding ring
found somewhere in the house.

384
00:25:17,015 --> 00:25:18,058
That would be…

385
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:21,895
Haruka herself.

386
00:25:21,978 --> 00:25:23,271
That's not true!

387
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,441
It was me.

388
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:28,526
I did everything.

389
00:25:34,532 --> 00:25:36,409
In this arson case,

390
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:40,372
the two of you conspired together.

391
00:25:42,999 --> 00:25:46,711
So, why did you do such a thing?

392
00:25:48,463 --> 00:25:52,759
<i>Haruka visited several orthopedic clinics</i>
<i>over the past few years.</i>

393
00:25:53,260 --> 00:25:55,553
<i>Her fracture from the fall</i>
<i>seemed unnatural,</i>

394
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:59,182
<i>and she had bruises that looked</i>
<i>as if she had been punched.</i>

395
00:26:02,143 --> 00:26:06,231
It seems Haruka was being
physically abused by Yasuyuki.

396
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:09,776
And you knew about it, right?

397
00:26:09,859 --> 00:26:11,695
I already told you I did it!

398
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:16,908
Since I'm admitting to it,
just hurry up and arrest me!

399
00:26:24,791 --> 00:26:27,252
The one who killed Miwa Tateno

400
00:26:28,169 --> 00:26:29,337
was neither you

401
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:31,381
nor Haruka.

402
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:33,425
Isn't that right?

403
00:26:36,219 --> 00:26:39,389
We obtained a warrant
and checked your dashcam.

404
00:26:41,474 --> 00:26:43,101
On the day of the incident,

405
00:26:43,184 --> 00:26:47,522
you two didn't want anyone to hear you
discussing the domestic abuse.

406
00:26:48,857 --> 00:26:50,442
That's why you went for a drive.

407
00:26:52,319 --> 00:26:54,404
You should really just go to the police.

408
00:26:54,988 --> 00:26:56,323
The police?

409
00:26:57,824 --> 00:26:59,451
But if I do that,

410
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:02,871
he really will kill me.

411
00:27:06,791 --> 00:27:08,626
But you have to run away.

412
00:27:11,421 --> 00:27:12,881
I can't.

413
00:27:14,507 --> 00:27:15,925
No matter where I go,

414
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:19,179
he will chase me down.

415
00:27:23,433 --> 00:27:25,477
<i>Contrary to your statement,</i>

416
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:28,730
<i>Natsumi was actually with you.</i>

417
00:27:29,856 --> 00:27:30,815
<i>And…</i>

418
00:27:31,399 --> 00:27:36,112
<i>when you went to drop off</i>
<i>Haruka and Natsumi…</i>

419
00:27:36,196 --> 00:27:37,697
There we go.

420
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:39,240
What snack do you want?

421
00:27:42,786 --> 00:27:43,953
What's wrong?

422
00:27:45,872 --> 00:27:46,706
Natsumi.

423
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:49,459
-Yes?
-Wash your hands and go upstairs.

424
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:02,389
She's dead.

425
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:05,809
The police…

426
00:28:06,684 --> 00:28:07,852
This is Miwa.

427
00:28:09,187 --> 00:28:10,146
What?

428
00:28:11,147 --> 00:28:12,565
You know her?

429
00:28:13,566 --> 00:28:15,485
We were classmates in high school.

430
00:28:15,568 --> 00:28:17,195
She comes to the clinic.

431
00:28:17,779 --> 00:28:19,406
Why is she…

432
00:28:20,573 --> 00:28:22,575
Anyway, the police…

433
00:28:22,659 --> 00:28:23,868
Wait!

434
00:28:28,456 --> 00:28:29,916
We have to do it.

435
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:32,335
This is your only chance.

436
00:28:35,296 --> 00:28:36,131
Kozue?

437
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:40,093
Haruka…

438
00:28:41,219 --> 00:28:42,595
You should die.

439
00:28:44,848 --> 00:28:46,641
What are you saying?

440
00:28:47,684 --> 00:28:49,936
We'll make it look like you died.

441
00:28:50,562 --> 00:28:53,064
Then, you can be reborn.

442
00:28:57,277 --> 00:28:58,528
And then,

443
00:28:59,028 --> 00:29:03,450
you two immediately
went through with the plan.

444
00:29:06,161 --> 00:29:11,082
<i>First, you got Natsumi out to the car</i>
<i>in a nearby parking lot.</i>

445
00:29:13,334 --> 00:29:14,252
<i>Then,</i>

446
00:29:14,961 --> 00:29:16,629
<i>you put on the wedding ring.</i>

447
00:29:18,882 --> 00:29:22,635
<i>And to completely burn away the body,</i>
<i>you doused her in kerosene.</i>

448
00:29:50,205 --> 00:29:51,206
Natsumi!

449
00:29:51,289 --> 00:29:52,373
My daughter…

450
00:29:52,457 --> 00:29:55,084
-My daughter is inside!
-What?

451
00:29:56,711 --> 00:29:59,631
<i>Of course, you could not fake</i>
<i>a child's remains.</i>

452
00:29:59,714 --> 00:30:02,467
<i>Therefore, you reported</i>
<i>to the fire department</i>

453
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:05,094
<i>that you saw Natsumi</i>
<i>trapped inside the house.</i>

454
00:30:06,012 --> 00:30:06,846
There's a fire.

455
00:30:06,930 --> 00:30:09,599
A girl is trapped inside,
and my friend went in there.

456
00:30:09,682 --> 00:30:10,809
Please hurry!

457
00:30:11,518 --> 00:30:16,231
<i>And, she escaped from the back door</i>
<i>before the fire truck arrived.</i>

458
00:30:17,106 --> 00:30:21,611
<i>She met up with Natsumi</i>
<i>and escaped in your car.</i>

459
00:30:28,034 --> 00:30:33,748
At first, we thought that you
and Yasuyuki were having an affair.

460
00:30:34,874 --> 00:30:36,709
But that wasn't the case.

461
00:30:38,211 --> 00:30:39,254
Kozue.

462
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:41,381
You…

463
00:30:43,508 --> 00:30:46,052
were trying to protect Haruka
and Natsumi, right?

464
00:30:46,135 --> 00:30:47,220
No!

465
00:30:48,179 --> 00:30:50,139
Quit saying all this nonsense!

466
00:30:50,223 --> 00:30:52,517
I did everything, it was me!

467
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:56,604
Haruka has nothing to do with it.

468
00:30:56,688 --> 00:30:58,398
Haruka… Haruka is…

469
00:30:58,481 --> 00:31:00,650
Your beloved partner.

470
00:31:02,151 --> 00:31:03,236
Right?

471
00:31:05,655 --> 00:31:07,073
She's the partner

472
00:31:08,157 --> 00:31:11,369
you've been fighting together with
all along, isn't she?

473
00:31:35,059 --> 00:31:36,185
I'm sorry.

474
00:31:40,148 --> 00:31:41,608
Haruka, I'm sorry.

475
00:31:43,484 --> 00:31:45,361
I couldn't protect you.

476
00:31:55,246 --> 00:31:56,456
You were

477
00:31:57,498 --> 00:32:00,835
about to go see Haruka
and her daughter, weren't you?

478
00:32:03,004 --> 00:32:05,715
Could you tell us their location?

479
00:32:08,635 --> 00:32:12,180
What will happen to Natsumi
if just the two of us are arrested?

480
00:32:14,682 --> 00:32:16,559
At this rate, Yasuyuki will…

481
00:32:16,643 --> 00:32:17,936
Don't worry.

482
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:20,647
I won't let that happen.

483
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:26,194
The police exist to protect
your loved ones.

484
00:32:27,070 --> 00:32:28,947
We will protect her.

485
00:32:30,573 --> 00:32:31,950
Please trust us.

486
00:32:55,473 --> 00:32:56,557
Go ahead.

487
00:32:58,434 --> 00:32:59,477
What?

488
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:01,187
You found Natsumi?

489
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:02,522
Yes.

490
00:33:02,605 --> 00:33:05,400
Where is she? Please let me see her.

491
00:33:05,483 --> 00:33:06,484
More importantly,

492
00:33:08,027 --> 00:33:13,741
there is suspicion against you
for physically abusing Haruka.

493
00:33:16,369 --> 00:33:17,870
What are you talking about?

494
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:20,623
I would never do that.

495
00:33:24,752 --> 00:33:27,922
Sure, we've had a couple of
marital disputes before.

496
00:33:29,382 --> 00:33:32,427
But anyone has those, don't they?

497
00:33:34,095 --> 00:33:35,388
Either way,

498
00:33:35,888 --> 00:33:37,849
please tell me where Natsumi is.

499
00:33:38,933 --> 00:33:41,310
She is my dearest daughter.

500
00:33:43,062 --> 00:33:44,814
I need to be with her.

501
00:33:44,897 --> 00:33:46,357
I can't do that.

502
00:33:47,775 --> 00:33:48,985
Why not?

503
00:33:49,485 --> 00:33:51,362
Because you

504
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:55,450
are the person who killed Miwa Tateno.

505
00:33:58,119 --> 00:34:02,290
You and Miwa had been having an affair
since last year's alumni association.

506
00:34:02,373 --> 00:34:03,249
This way, please.

507
00:34:04,792 --> 00:34:05,752
Thank you.

508
00:34:09,922 --> 00:34:13,301
<i>But she became dissatisfied</i>
<i>with that relationship…</i>

509
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:14,260
What's wrong?

510
00:34:14,343 --> 00:34:16,554
No, nothing. What shall we eat?

511
00:34:16,637 --> 00:34:20,266
<i>…and her behavior gradually escalated.</i>

512
00:34:22,185 --> 00:34:25,438
We have also found the message exchange
between Miwa and you.

513
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:27,356
On the night of the incident,

514
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,942
while Haruka and her daughter were away,

515
00:34:30,026 --> 00:34:32,487
she seems to have barged into your house.

516
00:34:34,614 --> 00:34:36,657
Cut it out already.

517
00:34:37,158 --> 00:34:40,119
Since you can't seem to break up yourself,

518
00:34:40,620 --> 00:34:42,497
I will tell your wife.

519
00:34:42,580 --> 00:34:43,915
Stop joking.

520
00:34:45,374 --> 00:34:47,210
I'm being serious!

521
00:34:47,293 --> 00:34:51,506
Shall I just go tell her myself,
or will you divorce her?

522
00:34:51,589 --> 00:34:53,132
Decide, now!

523
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:57,804
Or…

524
00:35:01,891 --> 00:35:03,392
shall we die together?

525
00:35:33,798 --> 00:35:35,716
<i>After you ran away,</i>

526
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:39,053
<i>you must have been surprised</i>
<i>to hear Haruka died in the fire.</i>

527
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:42,640
Eyewitnesses report seeing
Haruka and Natsumi taken by the fire.

528
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:45,434
That's not true.

529
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:49,438
It can't be true.

530
00:35:49,522 --> 00:35:53,401
<i>But upon seeing the wedding ring,</i>
<i>which she shouldn't have been wearing,</i>

531
00:35:53,985 --> 00:35:56,571
<i>you realized the swap Haruka pulled off.</i>

532
00:35:57,530 --> 00:35:58,614
<i>And then, you…</i>

533
00:35:59,198 --> 00:36:00,324
I know about you and Haruka.

534
00:36:00,408 --> 00:36:01,701
And you?

535
00:36:02,994 --> 00:36:04,495
You're relieved, aren't you?

536
00:36:05,079 --> 00:36:06,664
The reason you went to see Kozue

537
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:12,879
was actually to get the whereabouts
of Haruka and your daughter, wasn't it?

538
00:36:18,759 --> 00:36:19,886
I admit

539
00:36:20,678 --> 00:36:23,931
that I ended up in that kind
of relationship with Miwa.

540
00:36:24,765 --> 00:36:25,683
But,

541
00:36:26,684 --> 00:36:28,394
I didn't kill her or anything.

542
00:36:30,730 --> 00:36:33,107
There's not a single piece
of evidence, right?

543
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:39,197
Because it all vanished in the fire.

544
00:36:48,414 --> 00:36:49,749
There is.

545
00:36:51,459 --> 00:36:52,835
We've got evidence.

546
00:36:57,173 --> 00:37:01,969
Where did you go after leaving the scene
following the murder?

547
00:37:02,678 --> 00:37:03,888
Upon investigation,

548
00:37:04,805 --> 00:37:07,350
we found out you went
to a home improvement center.

549
00:37:08,935 --> 00:37:11,896
You purchased plastic buckets,
a shovel, and so on.

550
00:37:11,979 --> 00:37:12,813
Also,

551
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:16,108
a large amount of industrial caustic soda.

552
00:37:16,192 --> 00:37:17,693
WORKERS HEAVEN
RECEIPT

553
00:37:17,777 --> 00:37:21,989
Originally used
for industrial cleaning tasks,

554
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:25,660
it seems it also has the effect
of dissolving skin and protein.

555
00:37:26,786 --> 00:37:31,791
Did you intend
to dissolve and dispose of the body?

556
00:37:32,375 --> 00:37:33,459
No.

557
00:37:34,377 --> 00:37:35,503
That's…

558
00:37:35,586 --> 00:37:37,088
That's not all.

559
00:37:42,009 --> 00:37:45,179
Our colleagues were persistent

560
00:37:45,263 --> 00:37:47,890
and examined the remains
over and over again.

561
00:37:49,558 --> 00:37:53,104
When analyzing the internal structure
with a micro-CT,

562
00:37:53,187 --> 00:37:57,942
we found a depression mark on the skull
that cannot be explained by heat.

563
00:38:01,529 --> 00:38:06,117
<i>It was a very small trace</i>
<i>that wouldn't normally be found.</i>

564
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:08,744
<i>But because of how skilled they are,</i>

565
00:38:08,828 --> 00:38:10,663
<i>they were able to find it.</i>

566
00:38:12,873 --> 00:38:15,209
Next is the identification
of the murder weapon.

567
00:38:15,876 --> 00:38:17,670
Next is the culprit.

568
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:23,426
They will not give up until they solve it.

569
00:38:31,225 --> 00:38:33,019
I promised you, didn't I?

570
00:38:33,102 --> 00:38:35,813
That we would get to the bottom of this.

571
00:38:37,606 --> 00:38:42,069
We will definitely protect them.

572
00:39:13,601 --> 00:39:14,852
Wait!

573
00:39:14,935 --> 00:39:17,480
Yasuyuki admitted to the crime.

574
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,398
Of course,

575
00:39:19,482 --> 00:39:22,902
you two also need to atone
for a serious crime,

576
00:39:23,736 --> 00:39:28,783
but I think he will be in prison
for a long time for murder.

577
00:39:34,413 --> 00:39:36,207
Thank you very much.

578
00:39:37,958 --> 00:39:39,251
Really.

579
00:39:40,544 --> 00:39:41,462
Not at all.

580
00:39:46,926 --> 00:39:48,094
Kozue…

581
00:39:54,183 --> 00:39:55,351
Thank you.

582
00:40:57,413 --> 00:41:00,082
Finally, we're done.

583
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:03,127
Shall we take a break?

584
00:41:03,210 --> 00:41:04,211
Yes.

585
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:06,380
Everyone, you all did such a great job.

586
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:08,132
Yes, we seriously did.

587
00:41:08,215 --> 00:41:10,801
I'm really glad the case was solved.

588
00:41:10,885 --> 00:41:13,554
I wonder if our investigation was useful.

589
00:41:13,637 --> 00:41:15,973
I don't want to search
for anything for a while.

590
00:41:16,056 --> 00:41:17,850
If you would like, please have some.

591
00:41:18,726 --> 00:41:19,643
What?

592
00:41:19,727 --> 00:41:21,395
Love-chan cookies.

593
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:23,772
-Cute.
-I've been hooked on them lately.

594
00:41:23,856 --> 00:41:25,149
Cookies, huh?

595
00:41:25,232 --> 00:41:26,066
Thank you.

596
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:27,735
-Thank you!
-Go ahead.

597
00:41:27,818 --> 00:41:30,237
Since everyone overused
their prefrontal cortex,

598
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:32,364
the brain must be craving sugar.

599
00:41:32,448 --> 00:41:33,949
I get that.

600
00:41:34,033 --> 00:41:35,910
-I'll have one more.
-Go ahead.

601
00:41:36,494 --> 00:41:38,996
You did a great job too, Ms. Kiryu.

602
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:42,750
Thank you very much.

603
00:41:50,674 --> 00:41:53,844
Somebody's loved one.

604
00:42:00,100 --> 00:42:01,143
Everyone

605
00:42:02,019 --> 00:42:04,688
felt the same way, huh?

606
00:42:32,049 --> 00:42:33,551
TAKASAKA FAMILY GRAVE

607
00:42:33,634 --> 00:42:37,721
We are here to protect
people's loved ones.

608
00:42:39,848 --> 00:42:41,517
You're suited to be a detective.

609
00:42:52,528 --> 00:42:55,739
Why did you have to die so soon?

610
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:13,591
What you said before

611
00:43:14,091 --> 00:43:15,968
about the meaning of a "loved one"…

612
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:18,262
In America,

613
00:43:19,096 --> 00:43:22,600
they call the deceased a "loved one."

614
00:43:23,434 --> 00:43:25,227
Does that mean someone…

615
00:43:26,895 --> 00:43:28,772
who was important…

616
00:43:30,107 --> 00:43:31,609
to someone else?

617
00:43:34,028 --> 00:43:36,071
I feel like I've also…

618
00:43:37,740 --> 00:43:41,577
managed to grasp
what that means to me, just a bit.

619
00:43:43,078 --> 00:43:44,246
That

620
00:43:44,747 --> 00:43:46,290
is a wonderful thing.

621
00:43:59,678 --> 00:44:02,222
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot! It's a tie!

622
00:44:02,306 --> 00:44:04,391
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

623
00:44:06,101 --> 00:44:07,853
Okay, one more time.

624
00:44:07,936 --> 00:44:09,146
Let's do it.

625
00:44:09,229 --> 00:44:10,147
All right!

626
00:44:10,981 --> 00:44:13,025
One, two! Rock, paper, scissors, shoot.

627
00:44:13,108 --> 00:44:14,276
It's a tie.

628
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:15,944
Yes!

629
00:44:16,028 --> 00:44:18,405
One, two! Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

630
00:44:20,532 --> 00:44:22,618
<i>If he'd asked someone for help,</i>

631
00:44:22,701 --> 00:44:23,952
<i>he might not have died.</i>

632
00:44:24,036 --> 00:44:26,121
<i>Can you cook next week, too?</i>

633
00:44:26,205 --> 00:44:27,998
You can still start over.

634
00:44:28,082 --> 00:44:31,335
<i>Mr. Susaki wasn't alone, was he?</i>

635
00:44:31,418 --> 00:44:34,922
<i>We have officially decided</i>
<i>to disband the MEJ.</i>

636
00:44:48,060 --> 00:44:50,896
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.
